results.name: a(n) = gcd(n, A064988(n)).
comment: a(n) > 1 if and only if the prime factorization of n contains at least two distinct primes, p and q, such that q = prime(p).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
Index entries for sequences computed from indices in prime factorization
program: (PARI) A318668(n) = { my(f = factor(n)); for (k=1, #f~, f[k, 1] = prime(f[k, 1]); ); gcd(n,factorback(f)); }; \\ After code in A064988.
